Medhi Benatia, who&rsquo;s been on loan at Juventus from FC Bayern M&uuml;nchen since the start of the season, is to move to Turin permanently. The Italian champions have taken up a clause in the loan contract to buy the 30 year-old Moroccan international. The total transfer fee is &euro;20 million, comprising the &euro;3 million fee for the loan this season and a fixed sum of &euro;17 million agreed by the two clubs.<br />
<br />
FC Bayern chairman Karl-Heinz Rummenigge said: &ldquo;I&rsquo;d like to thank Medhi Benatai for two successful years at FC Bayern M&uuml;nchen and wish him well for his future at Juventus &ndash; particularly for the upcoming Champions League final on 3rd June against Real Madrid.&rdquo;
